--> Web : 
Web is an information space, which comprises of documents and web resources and are interlinked by hyper links and have some specific url, which are access via internet.

--> Web Page :
1. Web page is a document which is written in a plain text.
2. Web page contains multi media content 
   |-- images |-- audio |-- video |-- animation |-- transition etc
3. Every web page have some specific URL(Uniform Resource Locator)
4. Must be deployed on atleast one server.

--> Website : 
    It is a collection of web pages.
    There are two types of website : 
        a. Static Website
            |-- One way communication takes place.
            |-- Content may not change soo frequently.
        b. Dynamic Website
            |-- Two way communication takes place.
            |-- Content may change accordingly.

Note : Dynamic Website is also known as Web application

--> Web Application : 
    Application which works on the browser and whose execution takes place on the server.It basically works on client server architecture.
      |-----------request-------->|  
    Client <------Http------> Server
      |<----------response--------|

    Here http is hyper text transfer protocol
         It is a stateless protocol
         ---x---------->
         ---x---------->
         -------------->

--> Server :
    Server is a highly configured machine, which stores data, performs processing on that data and helps in retrieval of data.
    There are two types of server : 
        a. Web server ----> web application
        b. Application server ----> Enterprise application

